Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[æn'tenə]
*danh từ, số nhiều là antennae
 ■râu (của sâu bọ)
 ■(radio) anten

Anh - Anh
antenna
■ noun (plural antennae-ni:)
1》 Zoology a long, thin sensory appendage found in pairs on the heads of insects and some other arthropods.
2》 (plural also antennas) chiefly N. Amer. or technical an aerial.
3》 (antennae) the faculty of instinctively detecting and interpreting subtle signs: his political antennae remain as sharp as ever.
Derivatives
antennaladjective
antennaryadjective
Origin
C17: from L., alt. of antemna 'yard' (of a ship), used in plural to translate Gk keraioi 'horns (of insects)'.

Kết hợp từ & Cấu trúc câu
antenna
n. (AE) a loop; TV antenna (BE has aerial)
